	(text "(2) The output of the INA826 is referred to the output reference (REF) terminal, which is normally grounded. This\n    connection must be low-impedance to maintain good common-mode rejection. Although 5 Ω or less of stray\n    resistance can be tolerated when maintaining specified CMRR, small stray resistances of tens of ohms in series\n    with the REF pin can cause noticeable degradation in CMRR."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 48.26 34.925 0)
		(effects
			(font
